adding to GitHub where repository already of same name created

Run these one at a time:

Step 1 — Navigate to the folder:

cd R:\CHERP_Shares2\Weiner_Mark\DBMGMT\Roberts\aaa_desktop\code_other\git\repository1\Rstudio

Step 2 — Initialize Git:

git init

Step 3 — Link to your GitHub repo:

git remote add origin https://github.com/cbrentroberts5/Rstudio.git

Step 4 — Stage all files:

git add .

Step 5 — Commit:

git commit -m "Initial commit"

Step 6 — Rename branch to main:

git branch -M main

Step 7 — Push to GitHub:

git push -u origin main

Run this to verify locally:

git log --oneline

This shows your commit history. You should see your "Initial commit" listed.

Then verify on GitHub by visiting:

https://github.com/cbrentroberts5/Rstudio
